title: Redshift UCTM: HDD Total Usage
agents: special
catalog: os/storage
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the total HDD usage on Redshift Networks UCTM devices.

 To make this check work you have to configure the related
 special agent {Redshift Networks UCTM}.

 The check reports total disk space, used space, and percentage utilization
 with standard filesystem metrics (fs_used, fs_size, fs_used_percent).

 Thresholds can be configured via the ruleset "Redshift UCTM HDD Usage".
 Default thresholds are {WARN} at 80% and {CRIT} at 90%.

discovery:
 One service is created if HDD usage data is available from the device.

item:
 None
